         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#ala2004">
            <ab>To Good Fortune. The <foreign xml:lang="la">magnificentissimus</foreign> Rhodopaios, the lover of his country and defender of the people, the originator of the generous gift of the summer Olympian bath, and giver of corn as well as founder, renewer of pleasures that had been forgotten, the never-to-be-forgotten benefactor to us in everything, privately and public—the city <supplied reason="subaudible">has honoured him</supplied> adorning him with a statue for the third time</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>For Rhodopaios, see <ref type="inscription" n="85" target="iAph050016"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="86" target="iAph050017"/>, and discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="VI.26" target=".xml"/>.</p>
         </div>
